        "body": "<p>Everybody and their mamas are into bitcoin and cryptocurrencies nowadays, but John Oliver and Keegan-Michael Key want  you to know what the heck you&rsquo;re doing before you invest.</p><p>Oliver&rsquo;s show, <em>Last Week Tonight</em>, recently dedicated an <a href=\"http://time.com/5195126/john-oliver-cryptocurrencies-last-week-tonight/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">episode </a>to technology, or as he called it &ldquo;the thing that will make television so high def that I will no longer be allowed to appear on it.&rdquo;</p><p>Inevitably, the bitcoin trend came up, and Oliver was less than enthusiastic about cryptocurrency. He said it combines &ldquo;everything you don&rsquo;t understand about money &hellip; with everything you don&rsquo;t understand about computers.&rdquo;</p><p>The media has been reporting on bitcoin for a while, and because the science behind blockchains can very quickly get complicated and boring, Oliver brought on <a href=\"https://blavity.com/no-one-was-rooting-harder-for-jordan-peele-at-the-oscars-than-keegan-michael-key\">Keegan-Michael Key</a> for a hilarious sketch meant to help all of us get a better handle on the future of money.</p><p>The comedian mocked a cryptocurrency investor at a conference that claimed investing in crypto would &ldquo;change the world as we know it&rdquo; in the middle of otherwise unintelligible yelling about &ldquo;bitconneeeect.&rdquo;</p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\"><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xK3yuxrmCac\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></span>\n<br></p><p>Key took the opposite approach and warned people to be &ldquo;craeful&rdquo; when investing in Bitcoin or any other cryptocurrency.</p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\"><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/g6iDZspbRMg?start=1355\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></span>\n<br></p><p>&ldquo;The crypto market is extremely volatile and insufficiently regulated,&rdquo; Key yelled. &ldquo;They pump and dump!&rdquo;</p><p>&quot;Investing in cypto could be like getting in on Google on the ground floor,&quot; Key added, before tempering that with, &quot;Or, it could be like getting in on Google Glass on the ground floor, and that turned out to be a one story building!&quot;</p><p>Think of Key&rsquo;s message before you let your homeboy convince you to invest your rent money into bitcoin.</p>",
